message: Implemented gulp tasks - build, devbuild, docs, lint, watch. Added temporary element and mixins to exercise the build. These can be removed from the project later. Run 'yarn install'
Add minimization via uglify to the build. Create source map files. Run 'yarn install' to update node_modules
Replace browserify with webpack. Build both minimized and non-minimized bundles.
Initial implementation of mixins for keyboard support in list-like components.
Enable build of elix when it is installed under node_modules. Remove distribution files from the repository. They must be built.
Add support for Travis CI builds and tests through Sauce Labs
Remove JSDoc build system and generated .md documentation files

Remove gulp tasks and dependencies (#31)

* Replace with ./tasks/*.js scripts
* Commands available via "yarn run"
Move dependencies to devDependencies and upgrade webkit (#32)

Use TypeScript compiler as a type checker for project's JavaScript source files.
Add declaration files for TypeScript.
Rename package to @elix/elix and set daily version template
Update to latest sauce-test-runner. Fix error handling in sauce-tests.js (#36)
Replace the use of yarn with npm 5 (#40)
Use npm 5 in demos. Update root package-lock.json
Fix false-positive sauce-tests reporting. Patch LabeledTabs unit test for Edge 15. (#42)
Prepare for publish to elix rather than @elix/elix (#45)

Fix documentation bugs (#48)

* Fixes #47 and remove engines from package.json

* Pin dependencies. Add support for building jsdocs

* Make buildDocsHelper a module for sharing eventually with elix.org

* Stub out failing transition effect tests

* Fix lint warnings

* Fix documentation bugs in symbols.js and AlertDialog.js
Remove lit-html as a dependency for now.

Switch to ESLint.
Fix many linting errors.

Have custom "props" members that don't require parameters be properties.
Much wrangling in OverlayMixin to restore focus.

Upgrade to latest TypeScript.
Turn on strict checks.
Fix some TypeScript errors.
Run headless tests, only in chrome for now.
Add a static server, which we can start programmatically.
Add a bit of docs and also `npm start` to make it easy to use what's there.
Move test runner into tasks dir.
Use a simple port, for serving the site locally.
Remove live-server and update sauce-tests to use static-server (#59)

Update build system to use webpack configuration file. Remove node-based build scripts (#60)

* Simplify build with webpack config, and remove old node-based build scripts. Fix sauce-tests, removing custom-elements-es5-adapter.js. Stub out Edge tests for now due to sauce servers not finding our tunnel server.

* Update .travis.yml to use node latest version 8 which should pull npm 5.6.0 or greater
Remove tasks/build.js and update npm build task to include eslint (#61)
Have lint task also invoke type checks via TypeScript.
Run eslint and tsc prior to sauce-tests in Travis. Add tsc to build (#68)
Run ci:fast on travis for PRs (#69)

Try define elix.js as the main package entry point.
Include all mixins/helpers in elix.js.
Drop use of Babel transforms only needed for IE 11.
Use native node fs functions instead of relying on fs-extra.
Add .js to import for browser compatibility.
Remove tooling (Babel, webpack) previously needed to build demos for older browsers that didn't support ES6 modules.
Fall back to TypeScript 2.8, as 2.9 currently generates a raft of spurious error messages. (The problem has been fixed, but doesn't appear to have landed in TS yet.)

Upgrade dependencies.
Bump version number in preparation for release.

Pin version numbers.
Fix type errors.
Try using Express to server static files for headless and Sauce Labs testing. Not working yet.
Remove build system for docs, which is now handled by site.
Switch to Express as a server for headless testing.
Experiment with providing TypeScript typings for components.
Trying to get TypeScript to find "types" field in package.json.
Update sauce connect binaries through use of Component Kitchen versions of sauce-test-runner and sauce-connect-tunnel
Add a "module" key to package.json for ES6 module-aware bundlers.
Start on a prepublishOnly script to generate auto-define modules for each component.
Fold generation of weekData.js into prepublishOnly script.
Clean up .gitignore. Drop prettier as an explicit dev dependency until we want to enforce it, e.g., in pre-commit hook.
Upgrade to TypeScript 3.7.2. Fix some (but not all) new type errors identified by TypeScript.
Get rid of all type errors for mocha and node by providing the types directly.
Import chai everywhere to make tsc happy :).
Make sure sinon types are known.
Remove node types, since I thought that's where assert came from, but it is from chai.
Make typechecks work on tests too
